# Backend guideline

## 1. General coding guidelines
- Write clean and understandable code
- Prioritize readability and maintainability in all code.
- Ensure function and variable names are clear and descriptive.
- Use concise, meaningful comments for complex logic.
- Follow PER-CS 2.0 and Symfony coding standards
- Use PHP 8.3 features
- Separate the code into small, reusable functions
- Separate of logic - don't write business or application logic in the controller
